The paper deals with compressive sensing and interpolation techniques for time delay estimation, which are commonly studied in the fields of information theory (cs.IT), signal processing (cs.SP), and machine learning (cs.LG). The authors also mention the use of band-excluded orthogonal matching pursuit, which is a popular algorithm in the field of sparse signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the numerical experiments involve solving an optimization problem, which is a common theme in numerical analysis (cs.NA).
